'''Shawn Valdez''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and an [[evacuation officer]] of the [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance Special Forces]] during the height of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Expertly trained to evacuate Rebel bases with maximum efficiency, Valdez oversaw the evacuation of the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command's]] [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] during the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], ensuring the safe evacuation of more than 86 percent of the base personnel and surviving SpecForce [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]].

==Biography==
{{Quote|It's a good bet the Empire knows we're here.''"<br />"''We better start the evacuation.|Han Solo and General Carlist Rieekan, regarding the evacuation of Echo Base|<ref name="ESB" />}}
[[File:Shawn-valdez.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Valdez at Echo Base]]
Shawn Valdez was a [[Captain/Legends|captain]] serving with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Because evacuation was routine for Rebel bases, [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command]] began providing specialized training in evacuation procedures to chosen [[Alliance Special Forces/Legends|Alliance Special Forces]] [[Officer/Legends|officers]] following the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. The Alliance then assigned these specially trained officers to high-priority bases. One of these SpecForce [[evacuation officer]]s was Valdez, who earned a position at the Alliance's headquarters of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Water/Legends|ice]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. During his [[Time/Legends|time]] on Hoth,<ref name="Who's Who in Echo Base" /> Valdez owned the [[R5-series astromech droid|astromech droid]] [[R5-M2/Legends|R5-M2]], who was specially programmed to plan [[Sublight engine/Legends|sublight]] tactical courses through [[Realspace/Legends|space]].<ref name="R5">{{CCG|set=Hoth Limited|cardname=R5-M2 (Arfive-Emmtoo)}}</ref><ref name="Fact File 37">{{FactFile|37|AST 5-6|Astromech Droids}}</ref>

When the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] discovered Echo Base's existence in<ref name="Who's Who in Echo Base" /> [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].</ref> the responsibility fell to Valdez to oversee the ice facility's rushed evacuation in the face of the imminent Imperial attack on Hoth.<ref name="Who's Who in Echo Base" /> Present in Echo Base's central [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]], Valdez issued orders to his subordinates, explaining the base's evacuation plan: two [[Snowspeeder/Legends|snowspeeder]] groups, including [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Group]], would stay behind to meet the Imperial invasion force while the base's [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]] of thirty [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|GR-75 medium transports]] would depart from the planet as soon as they were loaded, carrying vital personnel and supplies.<ref name="ESB" />

Valdez played a major role in helping Echo Base evacuate during the ensuing [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]],<ref name="SWE">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' {{C|"Valdez, Shawn"}}</ref> with assistance from R5-M2, who provided tactical support to Valdez and planned evacuation routes from the base.<ref name="Fact File 37" /> As a testament to his efficiency and training, Valdez was able to ensure the safe evacuation of more than 86 percent of Echo Base personnel and surviving SpecForce [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]].<ref name="Who's Who in Echo Base" />

==Personality and traits==
Valdez was a popular and charismatic leader of Echo Base's [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]]. Well-trained to evacuate Rebel installations with maximum efficiency, Valdez's expertise and experience as an evacuation officer greatly served the Rebel Alliance during the Battle of Hoth. Valdez was also a [[Poet/Legends|poet]] and a [[Musician/Legends|musician]].<ref name="SWE" /> A [[Human/Legends|Human]], he had light skin.<ref name="ESB" />

==Equipment==
During his tenure on Hoth, Valdez wore the Rebellion's standard Echo Base [[Alliance Cold Weather armor|cold-weather armor]]. His [[Armor/Legends|suit]] included [[Alliance Cold Weather Headgear|headgear]], [[Anti-glare goggles/Legends|anti-glare goggles]], a [[Scarf/Legends|scarf]], [[Alliance Cold Weather armor|padded vest]], [[Alliance Cold Weather armor|padded tunic]], [[Alliance Cold Weather armor|gloves]], and [[Alliance Cold Weather armor|leggings]].<ref name="ESB" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|It's okay. I really just wanted to play.|The real Shawn Valdez|<ref name="Shawn Valdez">{{InsiderCite|34|A Real-Life Star Wars Hero: Shawn Valdez|A Real-Life ''Star Wars'' Hero: Shawn Valdez}}</ref>}}
[[File:Shawn_Valdez.jpg|thumb|right|190px|The real Shawn Valdez]]
Shawn Valdez first appeared in the [[1980]] film [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], portrayed by uncredited<ref name="ESB" /> ''[[Star Wars]]'' visual effects art director [[Joe Johnston]]. Each of the Echo Base extras in the brief scene in which Valdez appears are, in fact, ''Star Wars'' matte artists, including conceptual artist [[Ralph McQuarrie]], [[Harrison Ellenshaw]], and [[Michael Pangrazio]].<ref name="McQuarrie interview">{{WebCite|url=http://www.ralphmcquarrie.com/interview/mcquarrie/interview.html|text=The Art by Ralph McQuarrie - Interview|work=ralphmcquarrie.com; "Ralph McQuarrie Illustrator" DVD|archivedate=20031027114053}}</ref> Johnston, who also has a cameo as a [[Death Star Trooper/Legends|Death Star trooper]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']],<ref name="Imperial Gunner">{{DB|organization|imperialgunner|Imperial gunner}}</ref> has gone on to direct such feature films as [[Wikipedia:Jumanji (film)|''Jumanji'']], [[Wikipedia:Jurassic Park III|''Jurassic Park III'']], and [[Wikipedia:Captain America: The First Avenger|''Captain America: The First Avenger'']].<ref name="Yahoo">{{WebCite|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/legendary-filmmaker-joe-johnston-reflects-on-designing-103214763857.html|text=Legendary Filmmaker Joe Johnston Reflects on Designing 'Star Wars' and Directing Robin Williams|work=Yahoo.com|archivedate=20180624083754}}</ref>

The character was first provided a name on the [http://www.starwarsccg.org/cardlists/images/starwars/Hoth-Light/large/shawnvaldez.gif "Shawn Valdez" card] as part of the [[November]] [[1996]] ''[[Hoth Limited]]'' expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]],<ref name="Valdez CCG">{{CCG|set=Hoth Limited|cardname=Shawn Valdez}}</ref> with the name synonymously used on a card for R5-M2 released in the same set.<ref name="R5" /> The character [[Tuckerization|was named for]] [[Shawn Valdez (real person)|Shawn Valdez]], a Jacksonville, Florida, boy who died from leukemia at the age of thirteen after a near eight-year struggle. Valdez was an avid fan of the ''Star Wars'' franchise and the trading card game. Dreaming of having his own ''SWCCG'' tournament rating on the Decipher website, Valdez died a day after attending a ''SWCCG'' tournament from which he had to leave early due to weariness brought on by his condition. Due to the efforts of [[Gregg Keefer]], who ran the tournament, and with [[Lucasfilm]]'s permission, Decipher agreed to name a ''Star Wars'' character in Valdez's memory. The card's text, which describes the Shawn Valdez character as a "leader" and a "poetic musician," is a direct tribute to Valdez for his courage and for poetry he contributed to a book titled ''I Will Sing Life'', compiled by children with life-threatening illnesses.<ref name="Shawn Valdez" />

A discrepancy exists over the character's [[Military rank/Legends|rank]] with the Rebel Alliance. The article [[Who's Who in Echo Base: The Unsung Rebels of the Battle of Hoth|''Who's Who in Echo Base'']] from [[Star Wars Insider 74|''Star Wars Insider'' 74]] identifies Valdez as a [[Major/Legends|major]] in the character's biographical section heading, but the biographical entry itself describes the character as a captain.<ref name="Who's Who in Echo Base" /> Given that all other sources, including the original ''The Empire Strikes Back'' film script, identify Valdez as a captain,<ref name="ESB junior novel">[[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back (junior novelization)|''Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back'' junior novelization]]</ref><ref name="ESB Notebook">''[[The Empire Strikes Back Notebook]]''</ref><ref name="Annotated Screenplays">''[[Star Wars: The Annotated Screenplays]]''</ref><ref name="BTM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> this article treats the captaincy rank as [[canon]]ical.

